SUMMARY:Fin-Verse: Building Money Skills
DESCRIPTION:What if learning about money felt less like a lesson and more like an adventure? \nIn this interactive workshop\, children explore how money works through games with real choices\, working up to planning their very own vacation budget using play currency. Along the way\, they solve mini challenges\, make team decisions\, and discover what it means to spend\, save\, and choose wisely. \nNo finance talk. No cautionary tales. Only hands-on practice and the occasional ‘aha!’ moment making everything click. \nSmart money habits start early\, and learning them can be fun! \nAround the World in 50 Sundays is a journey that begins\, not with a ticket\, but with opening a book. In a city like Bangalore where families are always in motion\, the BIC Library hopes to offer stillness and a quiet\, welcoming space for both parents and children where reading becomes a shared way of being and not a task. \nEvery Sunday\, we open our doors to invite you into a library that listens; building a rhythm of return\, a habit of joy and a new community bound not just by books\, but by the weekly ritual of reading together. \nWe welcome your ideas and input. If you have suggestions for children’s events or activities that align with this vision\, we’d love to hear from you. Please reach out to us at library@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org \nSupported by: \n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/fin-verse-building-money-skills/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Around the World in 50 Sundays
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Thumbnail-Fin-Verse.jpg
END:VEVENT
