SUMMARY:Sole to Soul
DESCRIPTION:Hip-hop started as a revolution: moving the body in unexpected ways\, breaking through oppression with expression.  \nThis workshop offers a gentle introduction to the foundations of hip-hop\,  from cultural origins to footwork and rhythms. Beginning with a discussion on the history and origins of this style\, the dancing that follows is contextualised. Participants will explore hip-hop rhythm and grooves\, as well as elements of house dance.  \nPlayful and expressive\, this event is for anyone who is interested in learning to dance without pressure. \nThis event is a part of our programming to celebrate World Dance Day 2026\, ‘The Many Lives of Dance’. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/sole-to-soul/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Dance,Workshops
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Thumbnail-1-1.jpg
